316
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:07,395
Now work that bag!
Work that bag, J-man!

317
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:10,398
Left hook!
Hook off the jab!
Straight left hand.

318
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:13,317
What do we love?
Pain!

319
00:19:13,402 --> 00:19:17,738
Work that jab!
Work that hook! Work that hook!
Okay, take a break, take a break.

320
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:29,584
[Jim]
Be right there.

321
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,384
Hi. Lloyd Dobler, sir.
How are you?

322
00:19:38,468 --> 00:19:40,469
Pleasure to meet you.
Hello, Lloyd.

323
00:19:40,554 --> 00:19:43,181
Hello. Heard about
the graduation present.
Really quite a car.

324
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:48,019
Look, I know you're busy.
You don't have to entertain me,
but, uh, you can trust me.

325
00:19:48,103 --> 00:19:52,315
I'll tell you about myself.
I'm 19, been overseas for
a couple semesters. Now I'm back.

326
00:19:52,399 --> 00:19:55,943
I'm an athlete, so I rarely drink.
Ever heard of kickboxing,
sport of the future?

327
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:58,654
Don "The Dragon" Wilson?
Benny "The Jet" Urquidez?
Murray Smith?

328
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:02,366
Champions of the sport?
I can see by your face, no.
My point is, you can relax.

329
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:05,244
Your daughter will be safe
with me for the next
seven to eight hours, sir.

330
00:20:05,329 --> 00:20:07,705
Fine, Lloyd.

331
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:09,832
Come in.

332
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:11,918
Thank you.

333
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:15,087
How you doin'?
Okay, fine.

334
00:20:15,172 --> 00:20:17,715
Is she around?
Yeah. Uh, honey?

